<doc id="576346" wikidata="Q726157" url="?curid=576346" title="Jean Rousseau (violist)">
<text>Jean Rousseau (1 October 1644 – 1 June 1699) was a French viol player, theorist, composer, and author remembered principally for his &quot;Traité de la viole&quot; (1687), a valuable source of information on the performance practices of his time, as well as on techniques used in the construction of viols .

Rousseau was a pupil of Sainte Colombe for just one month, as the culmination of three years&#x27; study of the viol, and later dedicated his &quot;Traité&quot; to him. In that work, Rousseau defended Sainte Colombe&#x27;s innovations in left-hand technique, and systematically refuted the attacks made by Le Sieur de Machy in the preface to his &quot;Pièces de violle&quot; (1685) .

==References==</text><links>
