<doc id="576378" wikidata="Q342946" url="?curid=576378" title="Grote Markt">
<text> (Dutch for &quot;Grand Market&quot;; ) is a common name of a centrally located historic market square in many cities in Belgium and the Netherlands.

* Grote Markt (Antwerp)
* Grote Markt (Brussels), also known as the Grand-Place
* Grote Markt (Haarlem)
* Grote Markt (Kortrijk)
* Grote Markt (Leuven)
* Grote Markt RandstadRail station

